      "content": "hey, i'm working on this RBAC system for our backend. the permission logic is getting a bit messy with the hierarchy so i need a robust checker. \n\ncan u implement the `check_permission` function for me? i need it to follow the hierarchy (Admin > Manager > Editor > Viewer) and also check if the user has the specific attribute required for the resource.\n\nhere is the setup and the tests i need to pass:\n\n```python\nclass User:\n    def __init__(self, user_id, role, attributes=None):\n        self.user_id = user_id\n        self.role = role  # 'admin', 'manager', 'editor', 'viewer'\n        self.attributes = attributes or []\n\nclass Resource:\n    def __init__(self, resource_id, required_role, required_attribute=None):\n        self.resource_id = resource_id\n        self.required_role = required_role\n        self.required_attribute = required_attribute\n\ndef check_permission(user, resource, action):\n    # TODO: Implement this\n    pass\n\n# --- TEST SUITE ---\n# Hierarchy: admin > manager > editor > viewer\n\n# Test 1: Admin should have access to everything\nu1 = User(user_id=101, role='admin')\nr1 = Resource(resource_id='res_01', required_role='editor')\nassert check_permission(u1, r1, 'read') == True\n\n# Test 2: Manager accessing editor resource\nu2 = User(user_id=202, role='manager')\nr2 = Resource(resource_id='res_02', required_role='editor')\nassert check_permission(u2, r2, 'edit') == True\n\n# Test 3: Editor accessing viewer resource\nu3 = User(user_id=303, role='editor')\nr3 = Resource(resource_id='res_03', required_role='viewer')\nassert check_permission(u3, r3, 'view') == True\n\n# Test 4: Viewer accessing editor resource (should fail)\nu4 = User(user_id=404, role='viewer')\nr4 = Resource(resource_id='res_04', required_role='editor')\nassert check_permission(u4, r4, 'edit') == False\n\n# Test 5: Attribute check (Manager needs 'dept_finance' for financial docs)\nu5 = User(user_id=505, role='manager', attributes=['dept_sales'])\nr5 = Resource(resource_id='res_05', required_role='manager', required_attribute='dept_finance')\nassert check_permission(u5, r5, 'view') == False\n\n# Test 6: Attribute check (Admin with correct attribute)\nu6 = User(user_id=606, role='admin', attributes=['dept_finance'])\nr6 = Resource(resource_id='res_06', required_role='manager', required_attribute='dept_finance')\nassert check_permission(u6, r6, 'view') == True\n\nprint(\"All tests passed!\")\n```\n\nlmk when u have the function ready. it's super important it passes all these exactly as written.",
